Granted, this restaurant has been my sole exposure to Ethiopian food, but it is _so_ good.
For around $15-19 you can get an _enormous_ tray full of 10 or so different veggie and lamb/beef dishes,  all on a bed of sour injeera bread.
Great for sharing between 4-5 people, with extra bread on the side.
As long as your dining company doesn't mind eating "with their hands," you'll have a delicious, fun meal.
Good thirst-quenching drinks too.
