Lalibela just has about a dozen or so meat and vegetable dishes.
Likely all that could be found at Blue Nile for a much lower price.
I can understand why people come here.
The food is good (the injera is certainly better than Blue Nile's), but the lack of service and the price are enough to keep me out of Lalibela for good.

